'''Browns Glacier''' ({{Coord|68|56|S|78|0|E|source:GNIS|display=inline,title}}) is a small [[glacier]] {{convert|4|nmi|km|0}} north of [[Chaos Glacier]], flowing westward into the northern extremity of [[Ranvik Bay]]. The glacier was charted by Norwegian cartographers from air photographs taken by the [[Lars Christensen Expedition]] (1936–37), and was further identified in [[John H. Roscoe]]'s 1952 study of this area from [[U.S. Navy]] [[Operation Highjump]] (1946–47) photography. It was named by Roscoe for Lieutenant (j.g.) [[Eduardo P. Brown]], U.S. Navy, photographic officer with the western task group of Operation Highjump.<ref name=gnis/>

